subject: p16043637
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest were obtained. Patient is status post median sternotomy and cardiac valve replacement. Dual lead left-sided pacemaker is seen with leads extending to the expected position of the right atrium and right ventricle. There may be minimal basilar atelectasis. No focal consolidation is seen. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The cardiac and mediastinal silhouettes are stable and unremarkable.
